Apologies for QXing a "Linkedin Indian account", but I really like how these memes always have the surreal quality of a Lovecraftian story where the more you look, the more bizarre it slowly starts to get and you get a slight sense of nausea and a vertigo. It's very Innsmouthian.

E.g. the rest are real people, but Italy is a statue for some reason and doesn't change in the before or after, one uses Arnold in both, but the rest use different men in each, he remains representative of Austria even if he no longer lives there, etc. It genuinely surprises you.

Like James Bond is supposed to be an international global spy, A Fistful of Dollars is a Spaghetti western made in Italy, but both are meant to represent "pre-globalization". And pre Arnold is in the USA. It almost feels like it's intentionally made to disorient you like a koan.
